      <div class="msgContentFrame">I've brought this up before a couple of times, but never in this sub-forum... <br /> <br />I think that there should be an option for controller users to be able to switch their action bar layout from a single row of 10 buttons to a 3x3 square. <br /> <br />I realize that you lose out on 1 button, but i think the trade off is worthwhile if you hear me out. <br /> <br />With the default position being in the center, it would allow a controller user to have access to any of their buttons within one to two button presses. One option i would prefer to include with this is to have the selector reset back into the default position after an action is selected. This, as with everything else i believe, could be an option. <br /> <br />The way i see this working practically is that the main auto attack would be set to the middle button. This would allow controller users to hit auto attack seamlessly between actions and since every other action (say TP moves) would be within predictable button combinations it allows the player to focus more on the battle and not on selector position. <br /> <br />I think that a trigger assigment could be implemented as well to allow controller users to swap between 1-3 action bars with ease (similar to how you can with cntl and alt bars currently) to further allow for seamless combat for controller users. <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1626858.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
